comments.body:
@vs-code-engineering hello 👋🏽 there, friendly helpful AI, it's a pleasure to meet you!

I hereby confirm that this issue also affects the latest stable release 1.104.3.

Would a PR to add support for this be welcome?

@space-japan-studios you're right that we are shipping the ARM versions of these libraries with the x64 build. The reason for this was to simplify our build process for our Universal build packaging. It's a point in time behavior because:
1.  the MSAL team _will_ give us an x64 binary in their next quarter
2. the change required to exclude these DLLs is non-trivial for us at this time, Apple doesn't make this easy...
3. the logic is safe... Looking at MSAL's code here:
   https://www.npmjs.com/package/@azure/msal-node-runtime?activeTab=code

   ... unfortunately it's not on GitHub.

   ```ts
   var msalNodeRuntime;
   try {
       msalNodeRuntime = require("./msal-node-runtime");
   }
   catch (_a) {
       // If DLLs can't be loaded export stub class instance to prevent static imports from throwing
       msalNodeRuntime = new DefaultMsalNodeRuntime();
   }
   ```

   We can see that the `require` if this native node module is wrapped in a `catch`

So you were right that this happens, but it shouldn't affect reliability of the extension.

As for your MCP stuff, I'd love to learn more so that we can try to find the real issue.

