here are the logs. However, i think i understand whats going on. The client is looking for a endpoint that doesn't exist on my auth server according to https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8414.

I have the /auth/.well-known/openid-configuration

So, the client gets the unexpected token <!doctype (likely a 404 page). Then falls back on localhost. That is my guess.
It also strips off the /auth/ path. not sure what do do about that. does the 8414 spec expect the .well-known to be at the root of the domain, or can we adjust the client to append the .well-known after the give /auth?

I can add the endpoint its looking for, but would be helpful, if it meets spec to not strip off the path portion.

